Subject: [PATCH] wifi: ath11k: mark private RX page-frag validation build

Expose a read-only module parameter for the guarded router A/B test.  The
deployment watchdog uses /sys/module/ath11k/parameters/private_rxfrag to
distinguish the staged candidate from the stock module if ath11k is reloaded
while the SSH path is unavailable.

A module parameter is used instead of MODULE_VERSION because this OpenWrt
kernel enables CONFIG_MODULE_STRIPPED, which removes version metadata.  This
validation-only marker is not part of the upstream private-cache change.

---
 drivers/net/wireless/ath/ath11k/core.c | 3 +++
 1 file changed, 3 insertions(+)

--- a/drivers/net/wireless/ath/ath11k/core.c
+++ b/drivers/net/wireless/ath/ath11k/core.c
@@ -26,6 +26,9 @@ MODULE_PARM_DESC(debug_mask, "Debugging mask");
 static unsigned int ath11k_crypto_mode;
 module_param_named(crypto_mode, ath11k_crypto_mode, uint, 0644);
 MODULE_PARM_DESC(crypto_mode, "crypto mode: 0-hardware, 1-software");
+
+static bool ath11k_private_rxfrag = true;
+module_param_named(private_rxfrag, ath11k_private_rxfrag, bool, 0444);
 
 /* frame mode values are mapped as per enum ath11k_hw_txrx_mode */
 unsigned int ath11k_frame_mode = ATH11K_HW_TXRX_NATIVE_WIFI;
